programme.title: Live Test Cricket
programme.sub-title: New Zealand v England: First Test Day One
programme.desc: New Zealand v England. Coverage of the opening day of the First Test at Eden Park in Auckland, where the two-match series gets under way. The tourists last visited New Zealand for a Test series back in March 2013, when remarkably all three matches were drawn, including the decisive Third Test on this ground. Black Caps opener Peter Fulton scored a century in both innings to put the home side on top, but a dogged 110 not-out from Matt Prior saved the series for England.
